    "country_code": null,
    "payload": {
      "item_type": "disturbance",
      "source": "jtwc_abpw",
      "source_key": "jtwc_abpw|south_pacific_area|invest_31p",
      "content_hash": "9e19290eccef8109",
      "platform_summary": "37.2S 176.5E | winds 38-43 kt | 993 mb | LOW",
      "platform_location": "37.2S 176.5E",
      "wind": "38-43 kt",
      "risk_48h": null,
      "risk_7d": null,
      "next_update": null,
      "raw_text": "(1) THE AREA OF CONVECTION (INVEST 31P) PREVIOUSLY LOCATED \nNEAR 34.9S 176.9E IS NOW LOCATED NEAR 37.2S 176.5E, APPROXIMATELY \n85.6 NM EAST-SOUTHEAST OF AUCKLAND, NEW ZEALAND. THE SYSTEM IS \nCURRENTLY CLASSIFIED AS A SUBTROPICAL CYCLONE, GENERALLY CHARACTERIZED \nAS HAVING BOTH TROPICAL AND MIDLATITUDE CYCLONE FEATURES. ANIMATED \nENHANCED MULTISPECTRAL SATELLITE IMAGERY (MSI) DEPICTS A VERY BROAD \nAND ELONGATED LOW-LEVEL CIRCULATION CENTER (LLCC) EMBEDDED WITHIN A \nSWIRL OF MID-LEVEL CLOUD BANDS APPEARING TO BECOME SHEARED AWAY IN THE \nUPPER LEVELS BY THE POLAR FRONT JET STREAM. ENVIRONMENTAL ANALYSIS \nREVEALS UNFAVORABLE CONDITIONS FOR DEVELOPMENT, CHARACTERIZED BY LOW \nTO MODERATE VERTICAL WIND SHEAR (15-20 KNOTS), MODERATE UPPER LEVEL \nPOLEWARD OUTFLOW, AND COLD SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURES (23-24 C) ALONG \nTHE COAST. GLOBAL MODELS AGREE ON A SOUTHEASTWARD TRACK OVER THE NEXT \n24-36 HOURS AS IT TRANSITS THE EASTERN PORTION OF NEW ZEALANDâS NORTH \nISLAND, TE IKA-A-MAUI. FOR HAZARDS AND WARNINGS, REFERENCE THE FLEET \nWEATHER CENTER SAN DIEGO HIGH WINDS AND SEAS PRODUCT OR REFER TO LOCAL \nWMO DESIGNATED FORECAST AUTHORITY. MAXIMUM SUSTAINED SURFACE WINDS ARE \nESTIMATED AT 38 TO 43 KNOTS. MINIMUM SEA LEVEL PRESSURE IS ESTIMATED TO \nBE NEAR 993 MB. THE POTENTIAL FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF A SIGNIFICANT \nTROPICAL CYCLONE WITHIN THE NEXT 24 HOURS REMAINS LOW.",
      "metadata": {
        "basin_section": "SOUTH PACIFIC AREA (WEST COAST OF SOUTH AMERICA TO 135 EAST)",
        "invest_id": "31P",
        "system_class": "SUBTROPICAL CYCLONE",
        "lat": -37.2,
        "lon": 176.5,
        "wind_kt_min": 38,
        "wind_kt_max": 43,
        "wind_kt": 43,
        "pressure_mb": 993,
        "development_phrase": "REMAINS",
        "development_level": "LOW",
        "bulletin_issue_at": "2026-04-12T06:00:00+00:00"
      }
